Here’s my recipe and cooking video for "𝐃𝐨𝐮𝐛𝐥𝐞-𝐛𝐨𝐢𝐥𝐞𝐝 𝐏𝐚𝐩𝐚𝐲𝐚 𝐌𝐢𝐥𝐤 𝐏𝐞𝐚𝐜𝐡 𝐆𝐮𝐦 木瓜牛奶炖桃胶” where I’ll show you how to make this nourishing dessert for mums on confinement and breastfeeding mums.
.

Papaya is believed to help in post-delivery recovery, as it is rich in vitamins & minerals that are beneficial for breastfeeding mums.
.

Peach Gum is believed to support good complexion, cleanse blood, and relieve stress.
.

Similac Mum, a low GI maternal milk, has an improved EyeQ Plus nutrition system with Natural Vitamin E & Lutein, along with DHA. Similac Mum is also the lowest in fat* and the most complete* maternal milk with 27 essential vitamins and minerals, and prebiotic (FOS). So, it can assist mums to meet their increased nutritional needs during breastfeeding, and mums can be assured they are #beingbestforbaby from the beginning!
. "𝐃𝐨𝐮𝐛𝐥𝐞-𝐛𝐨𝐢𝐥𝐞𝐝 𝐏𝐚𝐩𝐚𝐲𝐚 𝐌𝐢𝐥𝐤 𝐏𝐞𝐚𝐜𝐡 𝐆𝐮𝐦 𝐑𝐞𝐜𝐢𝐩𝐞 𝐛𝐲 𝐁𝐚𝐤𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐓𝐚𝐢𝐭𝐚𝐢”
.
𝙄𝙣𝙜𝙧𝙚𝙙𝙞𝙚𝙣𝙩𝙨: (1 serving)
80g papaya (firm & ripe, skin & seeds removed)
15g peach gum
8g rock sugar
3 red dates, pitted & halved
200ml cool boiled water
3 scoops of Similac Mum vanilla milk powder
.

𝙈𝙚𝙩𝙝𝙤𝙙𝙨:.
1. Soak peach gum in water overnight till it expands and is soft to touch. Remove the impurities and rinse clean.
.
𝙉𝙤𝙩𝙚: Higher grade quality peach gum will have lesser impurities.
.
2. Bring a pot of water to boil. Put soaked peach gum, papaya, rock sugar, red dates, and 100ml water into a double boiler pot. Cover and double boil for 1hr 30 mins.
.
3. In a separate cup, mix 3 level scoops of Similac Mum milk powder with 100ml of water. Add into the double boiler and cook for 2 more minutes and it’s ready to serve.
.
*Comparison among all maternal milk in Singapore as of January 2020 both per 100 g of powder and per serving.
.
